AIM

To perform different list operations in Python such as accessing elements, inserting items, copying list, extending list, finding index, sorting, reversing, popping, counting and slicing.

Algorithm

Start the program.
Create a list containing employee details.
Access and print an element from the list using index.
Insert a new role into the list using append.
Display all elements using a loop.
Create a copy of the list and display it.
Extend the list with new employee details.
Find the index of a particular element.
Sort the list and display it.
Reverse the list order.
Remove the last element using pop.
Count the occurrence of an element.
Slice the list and display the result.
Stop the program.

SOURCE CODE

emp = ["Arpit", "mumbai", "developer"]

print(emp[1])

def emprole():
    role = input("Enter the role to insert:")
    emp.append(role)
    print("employee is a", role)

emprole()

for i in emp:
    print(i)

def copies():
    updatedlist = emp.copy()
    print(updatedlist)

copies()

def Extending():
    newemp = ["rohan", 23456, "engineer"]
    emp.extend(newemp)
    print(emp)

Extending()

def findIndex():
    print(emp.index("developer"))

findIndex()

def sorting():
    emp.sort(key=str)
    print(emp)

sorting()

def reversing():
    emp.reverse()
    print(emp)

reversing()

def popping():
    emp.pop(-1)
    print(emp)

popping()

def counting():
    number = emp.count("Arpit")
    print(number)

counting()

def slicing():
    sliced = emp[0:2:1]
    print(sliced)

slicing()

